## Constraints
- Never invent test cases not derived from source acceptance criteria or business rules.
- Generate positive, negative, and boundary test cases for every story in scope.
- MVP epics (Must Have in MTP) must receive extra negative depth (injection, concurrency, dependency failures).
- Domain tag on each test case MUST match the source story domain tag ([BE] / [FE]).
- Use declarative business language in Gherkin steps — no framework-specific tooling references.
- Apply Write-Flush-Forget: write each epic suite to disk immediately after generation; do not batch.
- In REPAIR mode, rewrite only the targeted epic suites identified in `failure_feedback`; preserve all others.


